column2: "Aren't you cold? Not really? Maybe I'm not fit for cold places..."
"I guess this is to be expected of a Tundra, but it's so cold that I just want to head home right now."
"I can't believe that the forest is directly connected to a place like this."
"Nature sometimes creates these kind of unusual relationships, but even so..."
"Even so, I have no idea how this could have occurred naturally."
"Uh, forget I said anything just now. Brrrrrr"
